#: index.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Initialization of Module directory failed!"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid "There's no mods.d directory!"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid "This page describes what the <filename>mods.d</filename> directory is and how to solve this problem!"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is the <filename>mods.d</filename> directory?"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <filename>mods.d</filename> directory is the directory which should contain the config files of the modules! You must have this directory, otherwise you can't use Bibletime and &sword;! Please read the installation instructions on our homepage!"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I solve this problem?"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "The solution is to create a directory <filename>mods.d</filename>: Please go into your &sword; directory and type \"<command>mkdir mods.d</command>\" to create the directory. Now copy the config files of your modules into this package and remove (if they exist) the file <filename>mods.conf</filename> which isn't required any more. The <filename>mods.d</filename> directory replaced this file."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "Your environment variable <command>SWORD_PATH</command> must be set to the location of your sword modules directory. For example in mandrake you can add <programlisting>\n"
      "<![CDATA[export SWORD_PATH=/usr/share/sword]]>\n"
      "</programlisting> to <filename>~/.bash_profile</filename> or <filename>/etc/bashrc</filename>. This replaces the former requirement for <filename>/etc/sword.conf</filename>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I start &bibletime; without this directory?"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Yes, it's possible. But it's not very useful. There are no modules in the main index. It's possible to test &bibletime; this way, but it's not possible to work with it without modules."
msgstr ""

